content:
Enable users to enter a website address by adding the URL element to your OmniScript. For example, a user can enter https://salesforce.com, or https://www.salesforce.com, and so on.

Drag a URL element from the Build panel onto the canvas.
In the Properties panel, give the element a name in the Name field.
In Field Label, enter a label visible to the user.
(Optional) In the Error Text field of the Validation Options section, enter text to override the default message displayed when the user does not enter the URL correctly.

URL properties are configurable from the Properties panel when you select a URL element. With the URL element, enable users to enter a web address in your OmniScript.
